01:13:33.890 --> 01:13:34.820
Yes!

01:13:40.550 --> 01:13:41.560
What is it?

01:13:41.760 --> 01:13:43.770
Nothing, my husband's downstairs.

01:13:43.880 --> 01:13:47.230
- Your husband!
- Yeah. Hurry up, come on, get dressed!

01:13:47.520 --> 01:13:49.630
What do you mean, "Hurry up"?
What husband?

01:13:49.730 --> 01:13:51.010
Please, hurry up!

01:13:51.110 --> 01:13:54.010
- He wasn't due back until Friday.
- But it's only Wednesday.

01:13:54.120 --> 01:13:57.530
Yeah, you want to ask him why?
He's six-foot-two and he's an airline pilot.

01:13:57.640 --> 01:14:00.360
If he finds you here, he's going to kill you.
Get dressed.

01:14:36.940 --> 01:14:38.880
What are you doing in my husband's robe?

01:14:38.990 --> 01:14:40.780
I'm not going to get caught half-dressed!

01:14:40.880 --> 01:14:43.940
Why play games?
I'll talk to him man to man, that's all.

01:14:44.050 --> 01:14:46.950
Are you crazy?
He's going to tear your balls apart!

01:14:47.050 --> 01:14:49.770
- What are you doing? Where are we going?
- Quickly, get outside!

01:14:49.870 --> 01:14:53.290
- This is a window!
- I know it's a window. It's this or the door.

01:14:53.390 --> 01:14:56.210
You must be joking! That's 100 feet down there.

01:14:56.300 --> 01:14:57.860
Please! I won't be very long.

01:14:57.970 --> 01:15:00.010
- Come on, Charlotte!
- I won't be long.

01:15:00.110 --> 01:15:02.670
He's probably got a taxi waiting.
He never stays long.

01:15:03.350 --> 01:15:04.770
Just stand out on the ledge.

01:15:05.170 --> 01:15:07.890
- Please, quickly. Don't worry. It's safe.
- God.

01:15:07.990 --> 01:15:11.020
- Now, just wait for me there.
- Jesus.

01:15:30.970 --> 01:15:32.460
Coming, darling.

01:15:47.420 --> 01:15:48.940
Get away.

01:16:05.340 --> 01:16:06.710
Who is that?

01:16:14.080 --> 01:16:15.190
My God!

01:16:35.840 --> 01:16:40.220
Better call the fire department!
There's a man about to jump off of that building!

01:16:57.700 --> 01:17:00.120
- What's up, babe? Where we goin'?
- Suicide.

01:17:11.010 --> 01:17:13.800
No! Not the ladder! It scares them.

01:17:13.890 --> 01:17:15.970
It makes them jump every time! Take it down!

01:17:16.070 --> 01:17:18.370
Take it out of here, take it down!

01:17:21.030 --> 01:17:23.300
Come on, people, a little cooperation here!

01:17:23.400 --> 01:17:27.330
Let's have some cooperation. This is
a dangerous area. We've got a man up there.

01:17:29.030 --> 01:17:31.460
Come on, folks.

01:17:36.010 --> 01:17:37.800
Come on, folks. Give us a break.

01:17:39.110 --> 01:17:40.460
Excuse me.

01:17:47.020 --> 01:17:48.480
Roger, we got it!

01:17:48.590 --> 01:17:50.250
- You got him?
- I got him.

01:17:53.160 --> 01:17:54.540
Come on, people.

01:17:55.020 --> 01:17:58.980
Okay, stand by.
Fine, we have reached the network.

01:17:59.790 --> 01:18:01.320
Stand by. Counting down.

01:18:01.420 --> 01:18:05.220
Five-four-three-two-one. You're on.

01:18:05.550 --> 01:18:08.580
Good morning.
This is Marvin Kausberg, Channel 5 news.

01:18:09.550 --> 01:18:11.280
That looks a little like Daddy.

01:18:11.380 --> 01:18:13.580
... a man was seen on the ledge of a ninth-floor...

01:18:13.680 --> 01:18:14.660
It does!

01:18:15.020 --> 01:18:17.410
The identity of the man is not yet known.

01:18:17.940 --> 01:18:22.280
The police have arrived and the fire department
suicide team, plus a substantial crowd.

01:18:22.830 --> 01:18:25.390
All of us waiting here,
in the small courtyard below...

01:18:25.490 --> 01:18:28.720
... are very unclear as to
what the man's motives are.

01:18:29.270 --> 01:18:30.670
He appears relaxed.

01:18:31.060 --> 01:18:35.020
In fact, he's seated on a small window sill,
smoking a cigarette.

01:18:35.120 --> 01:18:37.360
But he looks disturbed by all the attention...

01:18:37.460 --> 01:18:40.460
... as he hides his face
and waves the crowd away.

01:18:40.560 --> 01:18:42.570
The police are trying to control the crowd...

01:18:42.680 --> 01:18:44.500
... who are now calling for the man to jump.

01:18:44.600 --> 01:18:46.190
The question being asked here today...

01:18:46.290 --> 01:18:49.640
... is whether this man
does or does not want to commit suicide.

01:18:50.360 --> 01:18:51.570
Teddy!

01:18:53.910 --> 01:18:55.320
Two, three.

01:18:58.070 --> 01:19:00.050
It'll be all right!

01:19:00.570 --> 01:19:02.870
We'll catch you!

01:19:09.110 --> 01:19:10.130
Dive!

01:19:19.900 --> 01:19:22.390
- Baby!
- That's so good.

01:19:33.280 --> 01:19:34.260
Yes!

01:19:40.610 --> 01:19:42.490
What the hell am I doing?

01:19:43.550 --> 01:19:45.370
I have a wonderful wife!

01:19:46.020 --> 01:19:47.030
Jump!

01:19:48.900 --> 01:19:51.130
I could have thrown my whole life away.

01:19:51.520 --> 01:19:52.890
And for what?

01:19:53.220 --> 01:19:54.560
A piece of ass.

01:20:09.570 --> 01:20:13.350
What's that girl doing?
What is she doing, taking more pictures?

01:20:13.640 --> 01:20:15.780
No, give me a break!

01:20:16.770 --> 01:20:18.080
She is cute, though.

01:20:18.920 --> 01:20:20.290
Look at those legs!

01:20:20.390 --> 01:20:23.360
Hey, come on, now, stop it. None of that stuff.

01:20:23.460 --> 01:20:25.920
I made a mistake, I learned my lesson...

01:20:26.020 --> 01:20:28.390
... and I will never do it again.
